{
  "id": "1781025618667",
  "title": "Targeted text setup prompts",
  "summary": "What are the right moments to prompt text set-up? Inconclusive.",
  "slug": "targeted-text-setup-prompts",
  "product_area": "Campaigns, Flows, Lists & segments",
  "test_topic": "Text adoption",
  "hypothesis": "<p>Most email accounts are not ready to adopt SMS too early in their lifecycle. Prompting too early creates friction and leads to unnecessary dismissals. Conversely, waiting too long misses high-intent moments that can meaningfully grow SMS adoption.</p><p>We believe that a systematic and account-level prompting framework that meets users at the right milestone and prompts them to activate only when they have demonstrated readiness will drive stronger long-term success for accounts who set up SMS. This experiment will target paying accounts that have not set up SMS yet. We will measure success using <strong>New SMS Sends</strong>, and monitor <strong>New SMS Consents, New SMS Flows, and New SMS Campaigns to ensure no negative impact.</strong></p>",
  "results": null,
  "learning": null,
  "notes": "<p>Team hypothesizes that <strong>contextual prompts could work better instead of specific targeting criteria</strong>. </p><p>The team proposed that the product expansion team to run another iteration with a different design to inform their intent engine design and interventions. </p><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"text-primary underline underline-offset-2 cursor-pointer\" href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1W0QDNBnSKind3_LtCGMfdZ2V8T-XIUtWjToM_1Czbyc/edit?tab=t.0#heading=h.7im5wdm4mkvu\">PRD</a> || <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"text-primary underline underline-offset-2 cursor-pointer\" href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1fNjbI23ddWy_KUE3-R5ezghV_YNvYJftierUX6cvqlE/edit?tab=t.0#heading=h.h06iwuzfunb3\">KBI analysis</a></p>",
